      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "While it is true that both sides accuse each other of using \"fake news\" as a weapon, the reality is that the term itself is a subjective label that doesn't capture the full scope of the problem. The core issue isn't just who is lying, but that the internet has created a chaotic environment where misinformation spreads faster than fact-checking can verify it. This fragmentation makes it incredibly difficult for any single side to claim the truth without appearing biased, which is why the concept of \"fake news\" has become less useful and more of a political battleground than a factual description.",
